# Notification System Guidelines

## Use Existing Notification Provider

The application has a centralized notification system in [App.jsx](mdc:apps/web/src/App.jsx) using `NotificationProvider`. Always use this instead of browser alerts.

## Implementation Pattern

```javascript
// ✅ Correct - Use notification context
import { useNotification } from '../contexts/notification-context.jsx';

const { showNotification } = useNotification();

// Success notification
showNotification({
  type: 'success',
  title: 'Éxito',
  message: 'Operación completada exitosamente',
});

// Error notification
showNotification({
  type: 'error',
  title: 'Error',
  message: 'Ha ocurrido un error inesperado',
});
```

## Notification Types

- `success`: Green notification for successful operations
- `error`: Red notification for errors
- `warning`: Yellow notification for warnings
- `info`: Blue notification for informational messages

## Spanish Messages

All notification messages must be in Spanish:

- ✅ "Agendamiento creado exitosamente"
- ✅ "Error al procesar la solicitud"
- ❌ "Appointment created successfully"

## Context Usage

The notification context is available throughout the app via:

```javascript
const notificationContext = useContext(NotificationContext);
```

## Avoid Browser Alerts

